                <div class="emp__main--container">
                    <p class="paragraph">Empathize (with students) is the first stage in course design thinking. In this stage, you acknowledge students (or other stakeholders) as the end-users of your design (i.e., your course) and learn about their experiences, perspectives, challenges, and needs related to your course context.

                    <br><br>    The use of "empathize" rather than "understand" signifies a deeper cognitive, and even emotional, connection beyond surface knowledge of a "typical student." Using "empathize" also signifies the differences in students, who may interact with your course in different ways, have different needs, and respond differently to changes you make.
                        
